In this statement, the President of the United States, along with his wife Michelle, extends their best wishes to the Orthodox Christian community on the occasion of Holy Friday and the Feast of the Resurrection. The President acknowledges the joyous nature of this time for millions of Orthodox Christians, but also emphasizes the importance of remembering the sacrifice made by Christ and the example it sets for humanity. The President also expresses concern for the persecution and violence faced by Orthodox communities, particularly in the Middle East and North Africa, and reaffirms the commitment of the United States to protecting universal human rights, including freedom of religion. The President concludes by celebrating the transformative power of sacrificial love during this season of hope and restoration.